{"TopicId":180078,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"SAS \u0026quot;broken\u0026quot;","CreatedByName":"Jebediah Kerman Jr.","CreatedById":189524,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-25T17:09:50Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jebediah Kerman Jr.","CreatedById":189524,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-25T17:09:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was trying to land my \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003Essto\u003C/abbr\u003E at the runway, but something was wrong with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E. While in space, I turned off \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and the craft started pitching down violently. When \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E was back on, I tried to\u00A0pitch up, but the craft didn\u0027t want to. Only down. It\u0027s definitely not a problem with the craft. I looked at the gauges on the left of my control interface, and on the pitch gauge, there was not only the yellowish marker that shows my \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E usage, but at the bottom of the gauge, there was also a lavender marker. Other than the color, it looked the same as the yellow-orange one. I turned off \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E again, and the orangey-yellow marker shot down and covered up the purple one. Like I predicted, the craft pitched down. Can someone tell me how to stop this? I clicked on the cockpit and it said: \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E Locked. Help!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-25T17:22:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you have a joystick or gamepad plugged in? This sounds exactly like that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-25T17:26:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you accidentally set your trim?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlt\u002BX clears it I think.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jebediah Kerman Jr.","CreatedById":189524,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-25T17:49:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am using a console, XBox 1 to be specific.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-25T18:09:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223493468\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180078\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221543168187\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022189524\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jebediah Kerman Jr.\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, Jebediah Kerman Jr. said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am using a console, XBox 1 to be specific.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have no idea what resets trim on Xbox. Anyone know?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"4x4cheesecake","CreatedById":187982,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-25T18:35:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuick, let\u0027s ask google^^\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EFound a post from bewing:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4490955811\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/170089-setting-clearing-trim-on-console-and-control-map/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3277883\u0026amp;embedComment=3277883\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:282px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRadial Preset -\u0026gt; left bumper \u002B L3 to clear the trim \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jebediah Kerman Jr.","CreatedById":189524,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-25T18:43:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-25T22:17:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso please note that most players never use trim. So a on/off toggle\u00A0was added to the settings to completely disable it. That way, you never have to worry about this happening again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}